arch:property.oc:show_val: Locus 6, 7.5 Y/R 4/6 (Munsell Strong Brown), was established when Loci 1 and 2 reached the same elevation and were united. It is the same dry, granular fill, and like Locus 1, contains ashlars and arch stones from the collapse of the Central Arch and supporting walls as well limestone capital fragments.
Phase XII: Use levels, robbing and abandonments continue.
Phase XI: Further collapse post CE 5th c., possibly the result of the earthquake of CE 512. The east Porch columns and Central Arch collapse and fluvial deposits continue to accumulate.
Post earthquake fill and debris accumulation.
Phase XIII: Major collapses continue into the Islamic period.
